{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773484488699,"sessionID":"ses_31416915cffeaA1eCO5cj4ROyq","part":{"id":"prt_cebe9b6f20010Z1aTw3MYw2PS6","sessionID":"ses_31416915cffeaA1eCO5cj4ROyq","messageID":"msg_cebe9a5e1001Q9tXHlB64SoUZ5","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01TocewCMeU42GMP8qr2AbEj","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/token-tracking/src/index.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/token-tracking/src/index.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: #!/usr/bin/env bun\n2: /**\n3:  * index.ts — CLI entry point for the wombo-combo agent orchestration system.\n4:  *\n5:  * Every command has a short alias (e.g., woco i = woco init, woco t ls = woco tasks list).\n6:  *\n7:  * Usage:\n8:  *   woco init                                         (alias: i)\n9:  *   woco launch --top-priority 3                      (alias: l)\n10:  *   woco launch --quickest-wins 5\n11:  *   woco launch --priority high\n12:  *   woco launch --difficulty easy\n13:  *   woco launch --tasks \"feat-a,feat-b\"\n14:  *   woco launch --all-ready\n15:  *   woco launch ... --max-concurrent 3 --model \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"\n16:  *   woco launch ... --interactive\n17:  *   woco resume                                       (alias: r)\n18:  *   woco status                                       (alias: s)\n19:  *   woco verify [feature-id]                          (alias: v)\n20:  *   woco merge [feature-id]                           (alias: m)\n21:  *   woco retry <feature-id>                           (alias: re)\n22:  *   woco abort <feature-id> [--requeue] [--output json]  (alias: a)\n23:  *   woco logs <feature-id> [--tail N] [--follow]      (alias: lo)\n24:  *   woco cleanup                                      (alias: c)\n25:  *   woco history [wave-id] [--output json]            (alias: h)\n26:  *   woco usage [--by <key>] [--since <date>] [--until <date>] [--format table|json]  (alias: us)\n27:  *   woco tasks list [--status <s>] [--priority <p>]   (alias: t ls)\n28:  *   woco tasks add <id> <title> [options]             (alias: t a)\n29:  *   woco tasks set-status <task-id> <status>          (alias: t ss)\n30:  *   woco tasks set-priority <task-id> <priority>      (alias: t sp)\n31:  *   woco tasks set-difficulty <task-id> <difficulty>   (alias: t sd)\n32:  *   woco tasks check                                  (alias: t ch)\n33:  *   woco tasks archive [task-id] [--dry-run]          (alias: t ar)\n34:  *   woco tasks show <task-id>                         (alias: t sh)\n35:  *   woco tasks graph [--ascii] [--mermaid]            (alias: t g)\n36:  *   woco completion <bash|zsh|fish>                   (alias: comp)\n37:  *   woco tui                                          (default when no args)\n38:  *   woco wishlist add \"idea\" [--tag <t>]               (alias: w a, wl a)\n39:  *   woco wishlist list                                 (alias: w ls, wl ls)\n40:  *   woco wishlist delete <id>                          (alias: w rm, wl d)\n41:  *   woco help                                         (alias: -h, --help)\n42:  *   woco version\n43:  *   woco -v\n44:  */\n45: \n46: import { resolve } from \"node:path\";\n47: import { existsSync, readFileSync } from \"node:fs\";\n48: import { loadConfig, validateConfig } from \"./config.js\";\n49: import { loadState, saveState } from \"./lib/state.js\";\n50: \n51: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n52: // Dev-mode guard: warn if running the global binary inside the wombo-combo repo\n53: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n54: \n55: function checkDevModeGuard(): void {\n56:   const cwd = process.cwd();\n57:   const pkgPath = resolve(cwd, \"package.json\");\n58: \n59:   // Are we inside the wombo-combo repo?\n60:   if (!existsSync(pkgPath)) return;\n61: \n62:   let pkgName: string | undefined;\n63:   try {\n64:     const raw = readFileSync(pkgPath, \"utf-8\");\n65:     pkgName = JSON.parse(raw).name;\n66:   } catch {\n67:     return;\n68:   }\n69:   if (pkgName !== \"wombo-combo\") return;\n70: \n71:   // We're in the wombo-combo repo. Is the source being run from a different location?\n72:   // import.meta.dir = directory of THIS file (index.ts). If it's under cwd,\n73:   // we're running local source (bun dev). If it's elsewhere (e.g. ~/.bun/install),\n74:   // we're running the globally installed binary.\n75:   const sourceDir = resolve(import.meta.dir);\n76:   const projectSrc = resolve(cwd, \"src\");\n77: \n78:   if (!sourceDir.startsWith(projectSrc)) {\n79:     console.warn(\n80:       \"\\x1b[33m[WARNING]\\x1b[0m You are running the globally installed woco binary \" +\n81:       \"inside the wombo-combo repo.\\n\" +\n82:       \"  Use \\x1b[1mbun dev <command>\\x1b[0m instead to run from local source.\\n\" +\n83:       \"  See AGENTS.md for details.\\n\"\n84:     );\n85:   }\n86: }\n87: \n88: import { cmdInit } from \"./commands/init.js\";\n89: import { cmdLaunch } from \"./commands/launch.js\";\n90: import { cmdResume } from \"./commands/resume.js\";\n91: import { cmdStatus } from \"./commands/status.js\";\n92: import { cmdVerify } from \"./commands/verify.js\";\n93: import { cmdMerge } from \"./commands/merge.js\";\n94: import { cmdRetry } from \"./commands/retry.js\";\n95: import { cmdCleanup } from \"./commands/cleanup.js\";\n96: import { cmdAbort } from \"./commands/abort.js\";\n97: import { cmdLogs } from \"./commands/logs.js\";\n98: import { cmdUpgrade } from \"./commands/upgrade.js\";\n99: import { cmdHistory } from \"./commands/history.js\";\n100: import { cmdCompletion } from \"./commands/completion.js\";\n101: import { cmdTasksList } from \"./commands/tasks/list.js\";\n102: import { cmdTasksAdd } from \"./commands/tasks/add.js\";\n103: import { cmdTasksSetStatus } from \"./commands/tasks/set-status.js\";\n104: import { cmdTasksSetPriority } from \"./commands/tasks/set-priority.js\";\n105: import { cmdTasksSetDifficulty } from \"./commands/tasks/set-difficulty.js\";\n106: import { cmdTasksCheck } from \"./commands/tasks/check.js\";\n107: import { cmdTasksArchive } from \"./commands/tasks/archive.js\";\n108: import { cmdTasksShow } from \"./commands/tasks/show.js\";\n109: import { cmdTasksGraph } from \"./commands/tasks/graph.js\";\n110: import { cmdTui } from \"./commands/tui.js\";\n111: import { handleQuestSubcommand } from \"./commands/quest.js\";\n112: import { cmdGenesis } from \"./commands/genesis.js\";\n113: import { cmdUsage, type UsageGroupBy } from \"./commands/usage.js\";\n114: \n115: import { ensureTasksFile } from \"./lib/tasks.js\";\n116: import type { Priority, Difficulty, FeatureStatus } from \"./lib/tasks.js\";\n117: import type { QuestHitlMode } from \"./lib/quest.js\";\n118: import { resolveOutputFormat, output, outputError, type OutputFormat } from \"./lib/output.js\";\n119: import { validateId, validateText, validateBranchName, validateDuration, assertValid } from \"./lib/validate.js\";\n120: import { findCommandDef, commandToSchema, allCommandSchemas } from \"./lib/schema.js\";\n121: import { buildToonSpec, renderToonLegend } from \"./lib/toon-spec.js\";\n122: import { addItem as addWishlistItem, deleteItem as deleteWishlistItem, listItems as listWishlistItems } from \"./lib/wishlist-store.js\";\n123: \n124: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n125: // Types\n126: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n127: \n128: export interface CLIArgs {\n129:   command: string;\n130:   subcommand?: string;\n131:   // Selection options (launch)\n132:   topPriority?: number;\n133:   quickestWins?: number;\n134:   priority?: Priority;\n135:   difficulty?: Difficulty;\n136:   tasks?: string[];\n137:   allReady?: boolean;\n138:   // Launch / runtime options\n139:   maxConcurrent?: number;\n140:   model?: string;\n141:   interactive: boolean;\n142:   dryRun: boolean;\n143:   baseBranch?: string;\n144:   maxRetries?: number;\n145:   noTui: boolean;\n146:   autoPush: boolean;\n147:   // Abort options\n148:   requeue: boolean;\n149:   // General\n150:   featureId?: string;\n151:   force: boolean;\n152:   // Output format\n153:   outputFmt: OutputFormat;\n154:   // Upgrade options\n155:   checkOnly: boolean;\n156:   tag?: string;\n157:   // Features subcommand extras\n158:   status?: string;\n159:   ready?: boolean;\n160:   includeArchive?: boolean;\n161:   title?: string;\n162:   description?: string;\n163:   effort?: string;\n164:   dependsOn?: string[];\n165:   // Logs options\n166:   tail?: number;\n167:   follow?: boolean;\n168:   // Compact output\n169:   fields?: string[];\n170:   // Graph options\n171:   ascii?: boolean;\n172:   mermaidRaw?: boolean;\n173:   graphSubtasks?: boolean;\n174:   // Browser verification\n175:   browser?: boolean;\n176:   // TDD verification\n177:   skipTests?: boolean;\n178:   strictTdd?: boolean;\n179:   // Agent selection (per-task override)\n180:   agent?: string;\n181:   // Quest-specific options\n182:   goal?: string;\n183:   hitlMode?: QuestHitlMode;\n184:   /** Quest ID to scope a launch to (--quest <id>) */\n185:   questId?: string;\n186:   /** Tech stack description for genesis (--tech-stack) */\n187:   techStack?: string;\n188:   /** Constraints for genesis (--constraint, can be repeated) */\n189:   genesisConstraints?: string[];\n190:   /** Skip TUI review (--no-tui for genesis) */\n191:   genesisNoTui?: boolean;\n192:   /** Tags for wishlist items (--tag, can be repeated) */\n193:   wishlistTags?: string[];\n194:   /** Usage command: group by field (--by) */\n195:   usageBy?: UsageGroupBy;\n196:   /** Usage command: start date filter (--since) */\n197:   usageSince?: string;\n198:   /** Usage command: end date filter (--until) */\n199:   usageUntil?: string;\n200:   /** Usage command: output format (--format table|json) */\n201:   usageFormat?: \"table\" | \"json\";\n202: }\n203: \n204: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n205: // Command & Subcommand Aliases\n206: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n207: \n208: /** Map of short aliases → canonical top-level command names. */\n209: export const COMMAND_ALIASES: Record<string, string> = {\n210:   i: \"init\",\n211:   l: \"launch\",\n212:   r: \"resume\",\n213:   s: \"status\",\n214:   v: \"verify\",\n215:   m: \"merge\",\n216:   re: \"retry\",\n217:   a: \"abort\",\n218:   c: \"cleanup\",\n219:   h: \"history\",\n220:   lo: \"logs\",\n221:   t: \"tasks\",\n222:   features: \"tasks\", // backward-compat full-word alias\n223:   q: \"quest\",\n224:   g: \"genesis\",\n225:   u: \"upgrade\",\n226:   d: \"describe\",\n227:   comp: \"completion\",\n228:   tui: \"tui\",\n229:   w: \"wishlist\",\n230:   wl: \"wishlist\",\n231:   us: \"usage\",\n232: };\n233: \n234: /** Map of short aliases → canonical tasks subcommand names. */\n235: export const SUBCOMMAND_ALIASES: Record<string, string> = {\n236:   ls: \"list\",\n237:   a: \"add\",\n238:   ss: \"set-status\",\n239:   sp: \"set-priority\",\n240:   sd: \"set-difficulty\",\n241:   ch: \"check\",\n242:   validate: \"check\", // backward-compat full-word alias\n243:   ar: \"archive\",\n244:   sh: \"show\",\n245:   g: \"graph\",\n246: };\n247: \n248: /** Map of short aliases → canonical quest subcommand names. */\n249: export const QUEST_SUBCOMMAND_ALIASES: Record<string, string> = {\n250:   c: \"create\",\n251:   ls: \"list\",\n252:   sh: \"show\",\n253:   pl: \"plan\",\n254:   a: \"activate\",\n255:   p: \"pause\",\n256:   co: \"complete\",\n257:   ab: \"abandon\",\n258: };\n259: \n260: /** Map of short aliases → canonical wishlist subcommand names. */\n261: export const WISHLIST_SUBCOMMAND_ALIASES: Record<string, string> = {\n262:   a: \"add\",\n263:   ls: \"list\",\n264:   rm: \"delete\",\n265:   del: \"delete\",\n266:   d: \"delete\",\n267: };\n268: \n269: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n270: // Arg Parsing\n271: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n272: \n273: export function parseArgs(argv: string[]): CLIArgs {\n274:   const args = argv.slice(2); // skip 'bun' and script path\n275:   const result: CLIArgs = {\n276:     command: args[0] || \"tui\",\n277:     interactive: false,\n278:     dryRun: false,\n279:     noTui: false,\n280:     autoPush: false,\n281:     requeue: false,\n282:     force: false,\n283:     checkOnly: false,\n284:     outputFmt: resolveOutputFormat(undefined), // auto-detect until --output overrides\n285:   };\n286: \n287:   // Resolve top-level command alias (e.g., \"i\" → \"init\", \"t\" → \"tasks\")\n288:   result.command = COMMAND_ALIASES[result.command] ?? result.command;\n289: \n290:   // If the command is \"tasks\", treat the second positional as the subcommand\n291:   let startIdx = 1;\n292:   if (result.command === \"tasks\") {\n293:     result.subcommand = args[1] || \"list\";\n294:     // Resolve subcommand alias (e.g., \"ls\" → \"list\", \"ss\" → \"set-status\")\n295:     result.subcommand = SUBCOMMAND_ALIASES[result.subcommand] ?? result.subcommand;\n296:     startIdx = 2;\n297:   } else if (result.command === \"quest\") {\n298:     result.subcommand = args[1] || \"list\";\n299:     // Resolve quest subcommand alias (e.g., \"c\" → \"create\", \"sh\" → \"show\")\n300:     result.subcommand = QUEST_SUBCOMMAND_ALIASES[result.subcommand] ?? result.subcommand;\n301:     startIdx = 2;\n302:   } else if (result.command === \"wishlist\") {\n303:     result.subcommand = args[1] || \"list\";\n304:     // Resolve wishlist subcommand alias (e.g., \"a\" → \"add\", \"ls\" → \"list\")\n305:     result.subcommand = WISHLIST_SUBCOMMAND_ALIASES[result.subcommand] ?? result.subcommand;\n306:     startIdx = 2;\n307:   }\n308: \n309:   for (let i = startIdx; i < args.length; i++) {\n310:     const arg = args[i];\n311: \n312:     // Helper: consume the next argument, or exit with a clear error\n313:     function requireValue(flag: string): string {\n314:       if (i + 1 >= args.length) {\n315:         outputError(result.outputFmt, `Flag ${flag} requires a value.`);\n316:       }\n317:       return args[++i];\n318:     }\n319: \n320:     switch (arg) {\n321:       // --- Selection options ---\n322:       case \"--top-priority\":\n323:         result.topPriority = parseInt(requireValue(arg), 10);\n324:         break;\n325:       case \"--quickest-wins\":\n326:         result.quickestWins = parseInt(requireValue(arg), 10);\n327:         break;\n328:       case \"--priority\":\n329:         result.priority = requireValue(arg) as Priority;\n330:         break;\n331:       case \"--difficulty\":\n332:         result.difficulty = requireValue(arg) as Difficulty;\n333:         break;\n334:       case \"--tasks\":\n335:       case \"--features\": // backward-compat alias\n336:         result.tasks = requireValue(arg).split(\",\").map((s) => s.trim());\n337:         break;\n338:       case \"--all-ready\":\n339:         result.allReady = true;\n340:         break;\n341: \n342:       // --- Launch / runtime options ---\n343:       case \"--max-concurrent\":\n344:         result.maxConcurrent = parseInt(requireValue(arg), 10);\n345:         break;\n346:       case \"--model\":\n347:       case \"-m\":\n348:         result.model = requireValue(arg);\n349:         break;\n350:       case \"--interactive\":\n351:         result.interactive = true;\n352:         break;\n353:       case \"--dry-run\":\n354:         result.dryRun = true;\n355:         break;\n356:       case \"--no-tui\":\n357:         result.noTui = true;\n358:         break;\n359:       case \"--auto-push\":\n360:         result.autoPush = true;\n361:         break;\n362:       case \"--requeue\":\n363:         result.requeue = true;\n364:         break;\n365:       case \"--base-branch\":\n366:         result.baseBranch = requireValue(arg);\n367:         break;\n368:       case \"--max-retries\":\n369:         result.maxRetries = parseInt(requireValue(arg), 10);\n370:         break;\n371: \n372:       // --- General flags ---\n373:       case \"--force\":\n374:         result.force = true;\n375:         break;\n376:       case \"--check\":\n377:         result.checkOnly = true;\n378:         break;\n379:       case \"--tag\":\n380:       case \"--release\":\n381:         // --tag is overloaded: for 'upgrade' it's a release tag (single string),\n382:         // for 'wishlist' it's a categorization tag (repeatable array).\n383:         if (result.command === \"wishlist\") {\n384:           if (!result.wishlistTags) result.wishlistTags = [];\n385:           result.wishlistTags.push(requireValue(arg));\n386:         } else {\n387:           result.tag = requireValue(arg);\n388:         }\n389:         break;\n390:       case \"--output\":\n391:       case \"-o\":\n392:         result.outputFmt = resolveOutputFormat(requireValue(arg));\n393:         break;\n394: \n395:       // --- Tasks subcommand options ---\n396:       case \"--status\":\n397:         result.status = requireValue(arg);\n398:         break;\n399:       case \"--ready\":\n400:         result.ready = true;\n401:         break;\n402:       case \"--include-archive\":\n403:         result.includeArchive = true;\n404:         break;\n405:       case \"--title\":\n406:         result.title = requireValue(arg);\n407:         break;\n408:       case \"--description\":\n409:       case \"--desc\":\n410:         result.description = requireValue(arg);\n411:         break;\n412:       case \"--effort\":\n413:         result.effort = requireValue(arg);\n414:         break;\n415:       case \"--depends-on\":\n416:         result.dependsOn = requireValue(arg).split(\",\").map((s) => s.trim());\n417:         break;\n418:       case \"--fields\":\n419:         result.fields = requireValue(arg).split(\",\").map((s) => s.trim());\n420:         break;\n421: \n422:       // --- Graph options ---\n423:       case \"--ascii\":\n424:         result.ascii = true;\n425:         break;\n426:       case \"--mermaid\":\n427:         result.mermaidRaw = true;\n428:         break;\n429:       case \"--subtasks\":\n430:         result.graphSubtasks = true;\n431:         break;\n432: \n433:       // --- Logs options ---\n434:       case \"--tail\":\n435:         result.tail = parseInt(requireValue(arg), 10);\n436:         break;\n437:       case \"--follow\":\n438:       case \"-f\":\n439:         result.follow = true;\n440:         break;\n441: \n442:       // --- Browser verification ---\n443:       case \"--browser\":\n444:         result.browser = true;\n445:         break;\n446: \n447:       // --- TDD verification ---\n448:       case \"--skip-tests\":\n449:         result.skipTests = true;\n450:         break;\n451:       case \"--strict-tdd\":\n452:         result.strictTdd = true;\n453:         break;\n454: \n455:       // --- Agent selection ---\n456:       case \"--agent\":\n457:         result.agent = requireValue(arg);\n458:         break;\n459: \n460:       // --- Quest-specific options ---\n461:       case \"--goal\":\n462:         result.goal = requireValue(arg);\n463:         break;\n464:       case \"--hitl\":\n465:         result.hitlMode = requireValue(arg) as QuestHitlMode;\n466:         break;\n467:       case \"--quest\":\n468:         result.questId = requireValue(arg);\n469:         break;\n470: \n471:       // --- Genesis-specific options ---\n472:       case \"--tech-stack\":\n473:         result.techStack = requireValue(arg);\n474:         break;\n475:       case \"--constraint\":\n476:         if (!result.genesisConstraints) result.genesisConstraints = [];\n477:         result.genesisConstraints.push(requireValue(arg));\n478:         break;\n479: \n480:       // --- Usage-specific options ---\n481:       case \"--by\":\n482:         result.usageBy = requireValue(arg) as UsageGroupBy;\n483:         break;\n484:       case \"--since\":\n485:         result.usageSince = requireValue(arg);\n486:         break;\n487:       case \"--until\":\n488:         result.usageUntil = requireValue(arg);\n489:         break;\n490:       case \"--format\":\n491:         result.usageFormat = requireValue(arg) as \"table\" | \"json\";\n492:         break;\n493: \n494:       // --- Positional (feature-id, title for add, etc.) ---\n495:       default:\n496:         if (!arg.startsWith(\"-\")) {\n497:           if (!result.featureId) {\n498:             result.featureId = arg;\n499:           } else if (!result.title) {\n500:             result.title = arg;\n501:           }\n502:         }\n503:         break;\n504:     }\n505:   }\n506: \n507:   return result;\n508: }\n509: \n510: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n511: // Help\n512: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n513: \n514: function cmdHelp(): void {\n515:   console.log(`\n516: wombo-combo — AI Agent Orchestration System\n517: \n518:   WOMBO COMBO! Parallel feature development with AI agents.\n519: \n520: Commands:                        (alias)\n521:   init                           (i)     Generate .wombo-combo/config.json in the current project\n522:   launch                         (l)     Launch a wave of agents to implement features\n523:   resume                         (r)     Resume a previously stopped wave\n524:   status                         (s)     Show the status of the current wave\n525:   verify                         (v)     Run build verification on completed agents\n526:   merge                          (m)     Merge verified branches into the base branch\n527:   retry                          (re)    Retry a failed agent\n528:   abort                          (a)     Kill a single running agent (--requeue to return to queue)\n529:   logs                           (lo)    Pretty-print agent logs for a feature\n530:   cleanup                        (c)     Remove all wave worktrees and multiplexer sessions\n531:   history                        (h)     List/view past wave results (stored in .wombo-combo/history/)\n532:   usage                          (us)    Show token usage statistics (--by, --since, --until, --format)\n533:   tasks                          (t)     Manage tasks file (see below; 'features' also accepted)\n534:   quest                          (q)     Manage quests (scoped missions; see below)\n535:   wishlist                       (w/wl)  Quick-capture ideas and wishes (see below)\n536:   genesis                        (g)     Run genesis planner (project-level decomposition into quests)\n537:   tui                                    Interactive TUI: browse tasks, select, launch, monitor\n538:   upgrade                        (u)     Check for updates and upgrade wombo-combo\n539:   describe                       (d)     Emit JSON schema or TOON legend (--output toon)\n540:   completion                     (comp)  Generate shell completions (bash, zsh, fish)\n541:   version                                Print version and exit\n542:   help                                   Show this help\n543: \n544: Tasks Subcommands:               (alias)\n545:   tasks list                     (ls)    List tasks (--status, --priority, --difficulty, --ready, --include-archive)\n546:   tasks add <id> <title>         (a)     Add a new task (--desc, --priority, --difficulty, --effort, --depends-on)\n547:   tasks set-status <id> <s>      (ss)    Change a task's status\n548:   tasks set-priority <id> <p>    (sp)    Change a task's priority (critical/high/medium/low/wishlist)\n549:   tasks set-difficulty <id> <d>  (sd)    Change a task's difficulty (trivial/easy/medium/hard/very_hard)\n550:   tasks check                    (ch)    Validate tasks file (schema, deps, duplicates, cycles)\n551:   tasks archive [id]             (ar)    Move done/cancelled to archive (--dry-run)\n552:   tasks show <id>                (sh)    Show task details\n553:   tasks graph                    (g)     Visualize dependency graph (--ascii, --mermaid, --subtasks)\n554: \n555: Quest Subcommands:               (alias)\n556:   quest create <id> \"Title\"      (c)     Create a new quest (--goal, --priority, --difficulty, --hitl)\n557:   quest list                     (ls)    List all quests (--status to filter)\n558:   quest show <id>                (sh)    Show quest details\n559:   quest activate <id>            (a)     Activate a quest (creates branch, sets status to active)\n560:   quest pause <id>               (p)     Pause an active/planning quest\n561:   quest complete <id>            (co)    Complete quest (merges branch into base; --force to skip merge)\n562:   quest abandon <id>              (ab)    Abandon quest without merging (--force to delete branch)\n563: \n564: Wishlist Subcommands:            (alias)\n565:   wishlist add \"idea text\"       (a)     Add a new wishlist item (--tag <tag> to categorize)\n566:   wishlist list                  (ls)    List all wishlist items\n567:   wishlist delete <id>           (rm/d)  Delete a wishlist item (supports short ID prefixes)\n568: \n569: Genesis Options:\n570:   --tech-stack <text>      Describe the tech stack (e.g., \"React, Node, Postgres\")\n571:   --constraint <text>      Add a constraint (can be repeated: --constraint \"...\" --constraint \"...\")\n572:   --model <model>          Model override for the genesis planner agent\n573:   --no-tui                 Skip interactive review, auto-approve all quests\n574:   --dry-run                Show proposed quests without creating them\n575: \n576: Selection Options (for launch):\n577:   --top-priority N         Select top N tasks by priority\n578:   --quickest-wins N        Select N tasks with lowest effort\n579:   --priority <level>       Filter by priority (critical/high/medium/low/wishlist)\n580:   --difficulty <level>     Filter by difficulty (trivial/easy/medium/hard/very_hard)\n581:   --tasks \"id1,id2\"        Select specific tasks by ID (--features also accepted)\n582:   --all-ready              Select all tasks whose dependencies are met\n583: \n584: Launch Options:\n585:   --max-concurrent N       Max agents running in parallel (default: from config)\n586:   --model <model>          Model to use (e.g., \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514\")\n587:   --interactive            Use multiplexer (dmux/tmux) TUI mode instead of headless\n588:   --no-tui                 Headless mode without neo-blessed TUI (periodic console dashboard)\n589:   --auto-push              Push base branch to remote after all merges complete\n590:   --dry-run                Show what would be launched without launching\n591:   --base-branch <branch>   Base branch (default: from config)\n592:   --max-retries N          Max retries per agent (default: from config)\n593:   --browser                Enable browser-based verification (run after build passes)\n594:   --skip-tests             Skip running tests during TDD verification\n595:   --strict-tdd             Strict TDD: fail verification if new files are missing tests\n596:   --agent <name>           Override agent definition for all launched tasks (name without .md extension)\n597:   --quest <id>             Scope launch to a quest (uses quest branch as base, applies quest constraints)\n598: \n599: General:\n600:   --force                  Force overwrite (e.g., for init) / skip prompts (e.g., for upgrade)\n601:   --output <fmt>           Output format: text (default on TTY), json (default when piped), or toon (WOMBO_OUTPUT=toon)\n602:   -o <fmt>                 Alias for --output\n603:   --dry-run                Show what would happen without performing the action\n604:   --fields <list>          Comma-separated fields to include (e.g., id,status,priority)\n605: \n606: Upgrade Options:\n607:   --check                  Only check for updates, don't install\n608:   --tag <tag>              Install a specific version (e.g., v0.1.0)\n609: \n610: Logs Options:\n611:   --tail N                 Show only the last N lines\n612:   --follow, -f             Stream new output as it arrives (like tail -f)\n613: \n614: Usage Options:\n615:   --by <key>               Group by: task, quest, model, provider, harness (default: total)\n616:   --since <ISO date>       Filter records from this date (inclusive)\n617:   --until <ISO date>       Filter records until this date (inclusive)\n618:   --format <fmt>           Output format: table (default), json\n619: \n620: Aliases (every command has a short form):\n621:   woco i                         woco init\n622:   woco l --all-ready             woco launch --all-ready\n623:   woco t ls                      woco tasks list\n624:   woco t a my-task \"Title\"       woco tasks add my-task \"Title\"\n625:   woco t ss my-task done         woco tasks set-status my-task done\n626:   woco q c my-quest \"Quest\"      woco quest create my-quest \"Quest\" --goal \"...\"\n627:   woco q ls                      woco quest list\n628:   woco q sh my-quest             woco quest show my-quest\n629:   woco w a \"Cool idea\"           woco wishlist add \"Cool idea\"\n630:   woco wl ls                     woco wishlist list\n631: \n632: Shell Completion:\n633:   eval \"$(woco completion bash)\"    # Bash: add to ~/.bashrc\n634:   eval \"$(woco completion zsh)\"     # Zsh:  add to ~/.zshrc\n635:   woco completion fish | source     # Fish (or save to ~/.config/fish/completions/woco.fish)\n636: \n637: Examples:\n638:   woco init\n639:   woco launch --quickest-wins 3\n640:   woco launch --priority high --interactive\n641:   woco launch --tasks \"auth-flow,search-api\" --max-concurrent 2\n642:   woco resume\n643:   woco status\n644:   woco verify\n645:   woco merge\n646:   woco retry auth-flow\n647:   woco abort auth-flow\n648:   woco abort auth-flow --requeue\n649:   woco abort auth-flow --output json\n650:   woco logs auth-flow\n651:   woco logs auth-flow --tail 50\n652:   woco logs auth-flow --follow\n653:   woco logs auth-flow --output json\n654:   woco cleanup\n655:   woco tasks list --status ready --priority high\n656:   woco tasks list --fields id,status,priority --output json\n657:   woco tasks add my-task \"My Cool Task\" --priority high --difficulty easy\n658:   woco tasks set-status my-task in-progress\n659:   woco tasks check\n660:   woco tasks archive --dry-run\n661:   woco tasks show my-task\n662:   woco history\n663:   woco history wave-2026-03-12-420\n664:   woco history --output json\n665:   woco usage                              # show total token usage\n666:   woco usage --by task                    # group by task\n667:   woco usage --by model --format json     # group by model, JSON output\n668:   woco usage --since 2026-01-01           # filter by start date\n669:   woco usage --since 2026-01-01 --until 2026-03-01  # date range\n670:   woco describe                           # list all commands as JSON\n671:   woco describe launch                    # describe a specific command\n672:   woco describe tasks add                 # describe a subcommand\n673:   woco describe --output toon             # emit TOON format legend/spec\n674:   woco quest create auth \"Auth Overhaul\" --goal \"Replace basic auth with OAuth2\" --priority high\n675:   woco quest list\n676:   woco quest activate auth\n677:   woco quest complete auth\n678:   woco genesis \"Build a SaaS dashboard with auth, billing, and analytics\"\n679:   woco genesis \"Modernize the frontend\" --tech-stack \"React, TypeScript, Tailwind\"\n680:   woco g \"Add multi-tenant support\" --constraint \"No breaking changes\" --constraint \"Keep backward compat\"\n681:   woco genesis \"...\" --dry-run\n682:   woco wishlist add \"Add dark mode support\" --tag ui --tag enhancement\n683:   woco wishlist list\n684:   woco wishlist delete a1b2c3d4\n685: `);\n686: }\n687: \n688: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n689: // Main\n690: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n691: \n692: async function main(): Promise<void> {\n693:   checkDevModeGuard();\n694: \n695:   const PROJECT_ROOT = resolve(process.cwd());\n696:   const args = parseArgs(process.argv);\n697: \n698:   // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n699:   // Input validation at the CLI boundary\n700:   // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n701:   if (args.featureId) {\n702:     assertValid(validateId(args.featureId, \"feature ID\"));\n703:   }\n704:   if (args.title) {\n705:     assertValid(validateText(args.title, \"title\"));\n706:   }\n707:   if (args.description) {\n708:     assertValid(validateText(args.description, \"description\"));\n709:   }\n710:   if (args.baseBranch) {\n711:     assertValid(validateBranchName(args.baseBranch, \"base branch\"));\n712:   }\n713:   if (args.effort) {\n714:     assertValid(validateDuration(args.effort, \"effort\"));\n715:   }\n716:   if (args.tasks) {\n717:     for (const fid of args.tasks) {\n718:       assertValid(validateId(fid, \"task ID in --tasks\"));\n719:     }\n720:   }\n721:   if (args.dependsOn) {\n722:     for (const dep of args.dependsOn) {\n723:       assertValid(validateId(dep, \"dependency ID in --depends-on\"));\n724:     }\n725:   }\n726: \n727:   // Validate numeric args are not NaN\n728:   const numericArgs: [string, number | undefined][] = [\n729:     [\"--top-priority\", args.topPriority],\n730:     [\"--quickest-wins\", args.quickestWins],\n731:     [\"--max-concurrent\", args.maxConcurrent],\n732:     [\"--max-retries\", args.maxRetries],\n733:     [\"--tail\", args.tail],\n734:   ];\n735:   for (const [flag, value] of numericArgs) {\n736:     if (value !== undefined && isNaN(value)) {\n737:       outputError(args.outputFmt, `${flag} requires a numeric value.`);\n738:     }\n739:   }\n740: \n741:   // Commands that don't need config loading\n742:   if (args.command === \"version\" || args.command === \"-v\" || args.command === \"-V\") {\n743:     const pkgPath = resolve(import.meta.dir, \"..\", \"package.json\");\n744:     const pkgFile = Bun.file(pkgPath);\n745:     try {\n746:       const pkg = await pkgFile.json();\n747:       console.log(`wombo-combo ${pkg.version ?? \"(unknown version)\"}`);\n748:     } catch {\n749:       console.log(\"wombo-combo (unknown version)\");\n750:     }\n751:     return;\n752:   }\n753: \n754:   if (args.command === \"help\" || args.command === \"--help\" || args.command === \"-h\") {\n755:     cmdHelp();\n756:     return;\n757:   }\n758: \n759:   if (args.command === \"describe\") {\n760:     // Schema introspection: `woco describe [command]`\n761:     if (args.outputFmt === \"toon\") {\n762:       // Emit TOON format legend — self-describing, cacheable by agents\n763:       const pkgPath = resolve(import.meta.dir, \"..\", \"package.json\");\n764:       let version = \"unknown\";\n765:       try {\n766:         const pkg = await Bun.file(pkgPath).json();\n767:         version = pkg.version ?? \"unknown\";\n768:       } catch {}\n769: \n770:       if (!args.featureId) {\n771:         // Full TOON spec (legend + all commands)\n772:         console.log(renderToonLegend(version));\n773:       } else {\n774:         // JSON structure for the full spec (--output toon with a specific command\n775:         // still emits JSON since TOON is a line-oriented data format, not a schema format)\n776:         const spec = buildToonSpec(version);\n777:         const cmdName = args.title\n778:           ? `${args.featureId} ${args.title}`\n779:           : args.featureId;\n780:         const cmdSpec = spec.commands.find((c) => c.command === cmdName);\n781:         if (!cmdSpec) {\n782:           outputError(args.outputFmt, `Unknown command: \"${cmdName}\". Run 'woco describe --output toon' to see the full TOON spec.`);\n783:           return;\n784:         }\n785:         console.log(JSON.stringify(cmdSpec, null, 2));\n786:       }\n787:       return;\n788:     }\n789: \n790:     if (!args.featureId) {\n791:       // No command specified — list all commands\n792:       console.log(JSON.stringify(allCommandSchemas(), null, 2));\n793:     } else {\n794:       // Describe a specific command. Handle compound names: \"features list\"\n795:       const cmdName = args.title\n796:         ? `${args.featureId} ${args.title}`\n797:         : args.featureId;\n798:       const def = findCommandDef(cmdName);\n799:       if (!def) {\n800:         outputError(args.outputFmt, `Unknown command: \"${cmdName}\". Run 'woco describe' to list all commands.`);\n801:         return;\n802:       }\n803:       console.log(JSON.stringify(commandToSchema(def), null, 2));\n804:     }\n805:     return;\n806:   }\n807: \n808:   if (args.command === \"init\") {\n809:     await cmdInit({ projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT, force: args.force });\n810:     return;\n811:   }\n812: \n813:   if (args.command === \"upgrade\") {\n814:     await cmdUpgrade({\n815:       force: args.force,\n816:       tag: args.tag,\n817:       checkOnly: args.checkOnly,\n818:     });\n819:     return;\n820:   }\n821: \n822:   if (args.command === \"completion\") {\n823:     cmdCompletion({ shell: args.featureId }); // first positional = shell name\n824:     return;\n825:   }\n826: \n827:   if (args.command === \"logs\") {\n828:     if (!args.featureId) {\n829:       outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco logs <feature-id> [--tail N] [--follow] [--output json]\");\n830:       return;\n831:     }\n832:     await cmdLogs({\n833:       projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n834:       featureId: args.featureId,\n835:       tail: args.tail,\n836:       follow: args.follow,\n837:       outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n838:     });\n839:     return;\n840:   }\n841: \n842:   // Everything else requires config\n843:   const config = loadConfig(PROJECT_ROOT);\n844:   validateConfig(config);\n845: \n846:   // Commands that operate on the tasks file — ensure it exists first\n847:   const needsTasksFile = new Set([\"launch\", \"resume\", \"verify\", \"retry\", \"tasks\", \"tui\"]);\n848:   if (needsTasksFile.has(args.command)) {\n849:     await ensureTasksFile(PROJECT_ROOT, config);\n850:   }\n851: \n852:   switch (args.command) {\n853:     case \"launch\":\n854:       // Apply browser verification override if --browser flag was passed\n855:       if (args.browser !== undefined) {\n856:         config.browser.enabled = args.browser;\n857:       }\n858:       try {\n859:         await cmdLaunch({\n860:           projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n861:           config,\n862:           topPriority: args.topPriority,\n863:           quickestWins: args.quickestWins,\n864:           priority: args.priority,\n865:           difficulty: args.difficulty,\n866:           features: args.tasks,\n867:           allReady: args.allReady,\n868:           maxConcurrent: args.maxConcurrent ?? config.defaults.maxConcurrent,\n869:           model: args.model,\n870:           interactive: args.interactive,\n871:           dryRun: args.dryRun,\n872:           baseBranch: args.baseBranch ?? config.baseBranch,\n873:           maxRetries: args.maxRetries ?? config.defaults.maxRetries,\n874:           noTui: args.noTui,\n875:           autoPush: args.autoPush,\n876:           outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n877:           agent: args.agent,\n878:           questId: args.questId,\n879:         });\n880:       } catch (err: any) {\n881:         outputError(args.outputFmt ?? \"text\", err.message);\n882:       }\n883:       break;\n884: \n885:     case \"resume\":\n886:       await cmdResume({\n887:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n888:         config,\n889:         maxConcurrent: args.maxConcurrent,\n890:         model: args.model,\n891:         interactive: args.interactive,\n892:         noTui: args.noTui,\n893:         autoPush: args.autoPush,\n894:         baseBranch: args.baseBranch,\n895:         maxRetries: args.maxRetries,\n896:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n897:       });\n898:       break;\n899: \n900:     case \"status\":\n901:       await cmdStatus({ projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT, config, outputFmt: args.outputFmt });\n902:       break;\n903: \n904:     case \"verify\":\n905:       await cmdVerify({\n906:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n907:         config,\n908:         featureId: args.featureId,\n909:         model: args.model,\n910:         maxRetries: args.maxRetries,\n911:         browserVerify: args.browser,\n912:         skipTests: args.skipTests,\n913:         strictTdd: args.strictTdd,\n914:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n915:       });\n916:       break;\n917: \n918:     case \"merge\":\n919:       await cmdMerge({\n920:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n921:         config,\n922:         featureId: args.featureId,\n923:         autoPush: args.autoPush,\n924:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n925:         model: args.model,\n926:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n927:       });\n928:       break;\n929: \n930:     case \"retry\": {\n931:       if (!args.featureId) {\n932:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco retry <feature-id>\");\n933:         return;\n934:       }\n935:       await cmdRetry({\n936:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n937:         config,\n938:         featureId: args.featureId,\n939:         model: args.model,\n940:         interactive: args.interactive,\n941:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n942:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n943:       });\n944:       break;\n945:     }\n946: \n947:     case \"cleanup\":\n948:       await cmdCleanup({ projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT, config, dryRun: args.dryRun, outputFmt: args.outputFmt });\n949:       break;\n950: \n951:     case \"history\":\n952:       await cmdHistory({\n953:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n954:         config,\n955:         waveId: args.featureId,\n956:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n957:       });\n958:       break;\n959: \n960:     case \"usage\":\n961:       await cmdUsage({\n962:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n963:         config,\n964:         by: args.usageBy,\n965:         since: args.usageSince,\n966:         until: args.usageUntil,\n967:         usageFormat: args.usageFormat ?? \"table\",\n968:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n969:       });\n970:       break;\n971: \n972:     case \"abort\": {\n973:       if (!args.featureId) {\n974:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco abort <feature-id> [--requeue] [--output json]\");\n975:         return;\n976:       }\n977:       await cmdAbort({\n978:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n979:         config,\n980:         featureId: args.featureId,\n981:         requeue: args.requeue,\n982:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n983:       });\n984:       break;\n985:     }\n986: \n987:     case \"tasks\":\n988:       await handleTasksSubcommand(args, PROJECT_ROOT, config);\n989:       break;\n990: \n991:     case \"quest\":\n992:       await handleQuestSubcommand({\n993:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n994:         config,\n995:         subcommand: args.subcommand ?? \"list\",\n996:         questId: args.featureId,\n997:         title: args.title,\n998:         goal: args.goal,\n999:         priority: args.priority,\n1000:         difficulty: args.difficulty,\n1001:         hitlMode: args.hitlMode,\n1002:         status: args.status,\n1003:         agent: args.agent,\n1004:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n1005:         force: args.force,\n1006:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1007:         fields: args.fields,\n1008:       });\n1009:       break;\n1010: \n1011:     case \"genesis\":\n1012:       await cmdGenesis({\n1013:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n1014:         config,\n1015:         vision: args.featureId,  // first positional arg is the vision text\n1016:         techStack: args.techStack,\n1017:         constraints: args.genesisConstraints,\n1018:         model: args.model,\n1019:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n1020:         noTui: args.noTui,\n1021:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1022:       });\n1023:       break;\n1024: \n1025:     case \"wishlist\":\n1026:       handleWishlistSubcommand(args, PROJECT_ROOT, config);\n1027:       break;\n1028: \n1029:     case \"tui\":\n1030:       await cmdTui({\n1031:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n1032:         config,\n1033:         maxConcurrent: args.maxConcurrent,\n1034:         model: args.model,\n1035:         baseBranch: args.baseBranch,\n1036:         maxRetries: args.maxRetries,\n1037:         autoPush: args.autoPush,\n1038:         skipTests: args.skipTests,\n1039:         strictTdd: args.strictTdd,\n1040:         agent: args.agent,\n1041:       });\n1042:       break;\n1043: \n1044:     default:\n1045:       if (args.outputFmt !== \"text\") {\n1046:         outputError(args.outputFmt, `Unknown command: ${args.command}`);\n1047:       }\n1048:       console.error(`Unknown command: ${args.command}`);\n1049:       cmdHelp();\n1050:       process.exit(1);\n1051:       return;\n1052:   }\n1053: }\n1054: \n1055: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1056: // Tasks Subcommand Router\n1057: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1058: \n1059: async function handleTasksSubcommand(\n1060:   args: CLIArgs,\n1061:   projectRoot: string,\n1062:   config: import(\"./config.js\").WomboConfig\n1063: ): Promise<void> {\n1064:   switch (args.subcommand) {\n1065:     case \"list\":\n1066:       await cmdTasksList({\n1067:         projectRoot,\n1068:         config,\n1069:         status: args.status as FeatureStatus | undefined,\n1070:         priority: args.priority,\n1071:         difficulty: args.difficulty,\n1072:         ready: args.ready,\n1073:         includeArchive: args.includeArchive,\n1074:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1075:         fields: args.fields,\n1076:       });\n1077:       break;\n1078: \n1079:     case \"add\": {\n1080:       if (!args.featureId || !args.title) {\n1081:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco tasks add <id> <title> [--desc <desc>] [--priority <p>] [--difficulty <d>] [--effort <e>] [--depends-on <ids>]\");\n1082:         return;\n1083:       }\n1084:       await cmdTasksAdd({\n1085:         projectRoot,\n1086:         config,\n1087:         id: args.featureId,\n1088:         title: args.title,\n1089:         description: args.description,\n1090:         priority: args.priority,\n1091:         difficulty: args.difficulty,\n1092:         effort: args.effort,\n1093:         dependsOn: args.dependsOn,\n1094:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1095:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n1096:       });\n1097:       break;\n1098:     }\n1099: \n1100:     case \"set-status\": {\n1101:       // The new status can come from the second positional (stored in args.title)\n1102:       // or from the --status flag\n1103:       const newStatus = args.title || args.status;\n1104:       if (!args.featureId || !newStatus) {\n1105:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco tasks set-status <task-id> <status>\");\n1106:         return;\n1107:       }\n1108:       await cmdTasksSetStatus({\n1109:         projectRoot,\n1110:         config,\n1111:         featureId: args.featureId,\n1112:         newStatus,\n1113:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1114:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n1115:       });\n1116:       break;\n1117:     }\n1118: \n1119:     case \"set-priority\": {\n1120:       // The new priority can come from the second positional (stored in args.title)\n1121:       // or from the --priority flag\n1122:       const newPriority = args.title || (args.priority as string | undefined);\n1123:       if (!args.featureId || !newPriority) {\n1124:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco tasks set-priority <task-id> <priority>\");\n1125:         return;\n1126:       }\n1127:       await cmdTasksSetPriority({\n1128:         projectRoot,\n1129:         config,\n1130:         featureId: args.featureId,\n1131:         newPriority,\n1132:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1133:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n1134:       });\n1135:       break;\n1136:     }\n1137: \n1138:     case \"set-difficulty\": {\n1139:       // The new difficulty can come from the second positional (stored in args.title)\n1140:       // or from the --difficulty flag\n1141:       const newDifficulty = args.title || (args.difficulty as string | undefined);\n1142:       if (!args.featureId || !newDifficulty) {\n1143:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco tasks set-difficulty <task-id> <difficulty>\");\n1144:         return;\n1145:       }\n1146:       await cmdTasksSetDifficulty({\n1147:         projectRoot,\n1148:         config,\n1149:         featureId: args.featureId,\n1150:         newDifficulty,\n1151:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1152:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n1153:       });\n1154:       break;\n1155:     }\n1156: \n1157:     case \"check\":\n1158:       await cmdTasksCheck({ projectRoot, config, outputFmt: args.outputFmt });\n1159:       break;\n1160: \n1161:     case \"archive\":\n1162:       await cmdTasksArchive({\n1163:         projectRoot,\n1164:         config,\n1165:         featureId: args.featureId,\n1166:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n1167:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1168:       });\n1169:       break;\n1170: \n1171:     case \"show\": {\n1172:       if (!args.featureId) {\n1173:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco tasks show <task-id>\");\n1174:         return;\n1175:       }\n1176:       await cmdTasksShow({\n1177:         projectRoot,\n1178:         config,\n1179:         featureId: args.featureId,\n1180:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1181:         fields: args.fields,\n1182:       });\n1183:       break;\n1184:     }\n1185: \n1186:     case \"graph\":\n1187:       await cmdTasksGraph({\n1188:         projectRoot,\n1189:         config,\n1190:         status: args.status as FeatureStatus | undefined,\n1191:         ascii: args.ascii,\n1192:         mermaid: args.mermaidRaw,\n1193:         subtasks: args.graphSubtasks,\n1194:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1195:       });\n1196:       break;\n1197: \n1198:     case \"help\":\n1199:     case \"--help\":\n1200:     case \"-h\":\n1201:       cmdHelp();\n1202:       break;\n1203: \n1204:     default:\n1205:       outputError(args.outputFmt, `Unknown tasks subcommand: ${args.subcommand}. Run 'woco tasks help' or 'woco help' for usage.`);\n1206:       return;\n1207:   }\n1208: }\n1209: \n1210: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1211: // Wishlist Subcommand Router\n1212: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1213: \n1214: function handleWishlistSubcommand(\n1215:   args: CLIArgs,\n1216:   projectRoot: string,\n1217:   _config: import(\"./config.js\").WomboConfig\n1218: ): void {\n1219:   switch (args.subcommand) {\n1220:     case \"add\": {\n1221:       // The wishlist text comes from the first positional arg (featureId)\n1222:       // and optionally continues into the second positional (title).\n1223:       // Combine them if both are present.\n1224:       const textParts: string[] = [];\n1225:       if (args.featureId) textParts.push(args.featureId);\n1226:       if (args.title) textParts.push(args.title);\n1227:       const text = textParts.join(\" \");\n1228: \n1229:       if (!text) {\n1230:         outputError(args.outputFmt, 'Usage: woco wishlist add \"Your idea here\" [--tag <tag>]');\n1231:         return;\n1232:       }\n1233: \n1234:       try {\n1235:         const item = addWishlistItem(projectRoot, text, args.wishlistTags);\n1236:         output(\n1237:           args.outputFmt,\n1238:           item,\n1239:           () => {\n1240:             console.log(`Added wishlist item: ${item.text}`);\n1241:             console.log(`  ID: ${item.id}`);\n1242:             if (item.tags.length > 0) {\n1243:               console.log(`  Tags: ${item.tags.join(\", \")}`);\n1244:             }\n1245:           }\n1246:         );\n1247:       } catch (err: unknown) {\n1248:         const msg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n1249:         outputError(args.outputFmt, `Failed to add wishlist item: ${msg}`);\n1250:       }\n1251:       break;\n1252:     }\n1253: \n1254:     case \"list\": {\n1255:       const items = listWishlistItems(projectRoot);\n1256:       output(\n1257:         args.outputFmt,\n1258:         items,\n1259:         () => {\n1260:           if (items.length === 0) {\n1261:             console.log(\"No wishlist items yet. Add one with: woco wishlist add \\\"Your idea\\\"\");\n1262:             return;\n1263:           }\n1264:           console.log(`Wishlist (${items.length} item${items.length === 1 ? \"\" : \"s\"}):\\n`);\n1265:           for (const item of items) {\n1266:             const tags = item.tags.length > 0 ? ` [${item.tags.join(\", \")}]` : \"\";\n1267:             const date = new Date(item.created_at).toLocaleDateString();\n1268:             console.log(`  ${item.id.slice(0, 8)}  ${item.text}${tags}  (${date})`);\n1269:           }\n1270:         }\n1271:       );\n1272:       break;\n1273:     }\n1274: \n1275:     case \"delete\": {\n1276:       if (!args.featureId) {\n1277:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco wishlist delete <id>\");\n1278:         return;\n1279:       }\n1280: \n1281:       // Support both full UUIDs and short prefixes\n1282:       const items = listWishlistItems(projectRoot);\n1283:       const match = items.find(\n1284:         (item) => item.id === args.featureId || item.id.startsWith(args.featureId!)\n1285:       );\n1286: \n1287:       if (!match) {\n1288:         outputError(args.outputFmt, `No wishlist item found matching: ${args.featureId}`);\n1289:         return;\n1290:       }\n1291: \n1292:       const deleted = deleteWishlistItem(projectRoot, match.id);\n1293:       if (deleted) {\n1294:         output(\n1295:           args.outputFmt,\n1296:           { deleted: true, id: match.id, text: match.text },\n1297:           () => {\n1298:             console.log(`Deleted wishlist item: ${match.text}`);\n1299:           }\n1300:         );\n1301:       } else {\n1302:         outputError(args.outputFmt, `Failed to delete wishlist item: ${match.id}`);\n1303:       }\n1304:       break;\n1305:     }\n1306: \n1307:     case \"help\":\n1308:     case \"--help\":\n1309:     case \"-h\":\n1310:       cmdHelp();\n1311:       break;\n1312: \n1313:     default:\n1314:       outputError(args.outputFmt, `Unknown wishlist subcommand: ${args.subcommand}. Run 'woco wishlist help' or 'woco help' for usage.`);\n1315:       return;\n1316:   }\n1317: }\n1318: \n1319: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1320: // Error Handlers & Entry\n1321: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1322: \n1323: // Global error handlers — prevent silent crashes\n1324: process.on(\"uncaughtException\", (err) => {\n1325:   console.error(`\\n[FATAL] Uncaught exception: ${err.message}`);\n1326:   console.error(err.stack);\n1327:   try {\n1328:     const state = loadState(process.cwd());\n1329:     if (state) saveState(process.cwd(), state);\n1330:   } catch {}\n1331:   process.exit(1);\n1332: });\n1333: \n1334: process.on(\"unhandledRejection\", (reason: any) => {\n1335:   console.error(`\\n[FATAL] Unhandled rejection: ${reason?.message || reason}`);\n1336:   if (reason?.stack) console.error(reason.stack);\n1337:   try {\n1338:     const state = loadState(process.cwd());\n1339:     if (state) saveState(process.cwd(), state);\n1340:   } catch {}\n1341:   process.exit(1);\n1342: });\n1343: \n1344: main().catch((err) => {\n1345:   console.error(\"Fatal error:\", err.message);\n1346:   process.exit(1);\n1347: });\n\n(End of file - total 1347 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/index.ts","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env bun\n/**\n * index.ts — CLI entry point for the wombo-combo agent orchestration system.\n *\n * Every command has a short alias (e.g., woco i = woco init, woco t ls = woco tasks list).\n *\n * Usage:\n *   woco init                                         (alias: i)\n *   woco launch --top-priority 3                      (alias: l)\n *   woco launch --quickest-wins 5\n *   woco launch --priority high\n *   woco launch --difficulty easy\n *   woco launch --tasks \"feat-a,feat-b\"\n *   woco launch --all-ready\n *   woco launch ... --max-concurrent 3 --model \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"\n *   woco launch ... --interactive\n *   woco resume                                       (alias: r)\n *   woco status                                       (alias: s)\n *   woco verify [feature-id]                          (alias: v)\n *   woco merge [feature-id]                           (alias: m)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773484488694,"end":1773484488698}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773484488751,"sessionID":"ses_31416915cffeaA1eCO5cj4ROyq","part":{"id":"prt_cebe9b7f7001sBXavJGfjV4aSr","sessionID":"ses_31416915cffeaA1eCO5cj4ROyq","messageID":"msg_cebe9a5e1001Q9tXHlB64SoUZ5","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_016cZZQBRwqkAzP8STHiaQPL","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/token-tracking/src/lib/monitor.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/token-tracking/src/lib/monitor.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * monitor.ts — Parse JSON events from agent and detect completion/failure.\n3:  *\n4:  * Responsibilities:\n5:  *   - Parse newline-delimited JSON events from agent stdout\n6:  *   - Detect session completion (agent finished)\n7:  *   - Detect session ID from events\n8:  *   - Detect errors and failures\n9:  *   - Write per-agent raw log files for diagnostics\n10:  *   - Maintain per-agent parsed activity log for TUI preview\n11:  *\n12:  * ## Process Lifecycle (audit: wave-detach-audit)\n13:  *\n14:  * ProcessMonitor manages the lifecycle of headless agent child processes:\n15:  *\n16:  * **Normal flow**: Agent stdout → JSON event parsing → callbacks → completion\n17:  *   1. `addProcess()` registers a ChildProcess and attaches stdout/stderr listeners\n18:  *   2. Stdout data is parsed line-by-line as JSON events\n19:  *   3. Callbacks fire: `onSessionId`, `onActivity`, `onComplete`, `onError`\n20:  *   4. On process exit (code 0 or sawFinalStop), `onComplete` is called\n21:  *   5. On process exit (non-zero, no final stop), `onError` is called\n22:  *\n23:  * **Teardown flow**: Parent quit → `killAll()` → SIGTERM to each child\n24:  *   1. TUI `onQuit` or SIGINT handler calls `monitor.killAll()`\n25:  *   2. `killAll()` iterates all processes and calls `remove(featureId)`\n26:  *   3. `remove()` sends SIGTERM to the child process (if still running)\n27:  *   4. The process map entry is deleted — no further events are tracked\n28:  *\n29:  * **Key behavior**: `remove()` and `killAll()` intentionally kill child\n30:  * processes. This is correct because headless agents are spawned with\n31:  * `detached: false` — they are tied to the parent and would die anyway\n32:  * when the parent exits. Explicitly killing them ensures a clean shutdown\n33:  * with proper state saving before the parent terminates.\n34:  *\n35:  * **Edge case**: If the parent is killed with SIGKILL (not catchable),\n36:  * child processes die with no cleanup. `woco resume` handles this by\n37:  * detecting orphaned worktrees with commits and re-verifying/re-launching.\n38:  */\n39: \n40: import type { ChildProcess } from \"node:child_process\";\n41: import { isProcessRunning } from \"./launcher.js\";\n42: import { mkdirSync, appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync } from \"node:fs\";\n43: import { resolve } from \"node:path\";\n44: import { TokenCollector, type UsageRecord } from \"./token-collector.js\";\n45: import { UsageStore } from \"./token-usage.js\";\n46: \n47: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n48: // Log directory name (configurable would be overkill here)\n49: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n50: \n51: const LOG_DIR_NAME = \".wombo-combo/logs\";\n52: \n53: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n54: // Types — OpenCode JSON Events\n55: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n56: \n57: export interface OpenCodeEvent {\n58:   type: string;\n59:   sessionID?: string;\n60:   timestamp?: number;\n61:   part?: {\n62:     type?: string;\n63:     tool?: string;\n64:     callID?: string;\n65:     text?: string;\n66:     reason?: string;\n67:     cost?: number;\n68:     tokens?: {\n69:       total: number;\n70:       input: number;\n71:       output: number;\n72:       reasoning: number;\n73:       cache?: {\n74:         read: number;\n75:         write: number;\n76:       };\n77:     };\n78:     state?: {\n79:       status?: string;\n80:       input?: Record<string, any>;\n81:       output?: string;\n82:       error?: string;\n83:     };\n84:   };\n85:   [key: string]: any;\n86: }\n87: \n88: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n89: // Event Parser\n90: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n91: \n92: export interface ParsedOutput {\n93:   sessionId: string | null;\n94:   completed: boolean;\n95:   errored: boolean;\n96:   lastError: string | null;\n97:   events: OpenCodeEvent[];\n98: }\n99: \n100: export function parseEvents(rawOutput: string): ParsedOutput {\n101:   const result: ParsedOutput = {\n102:     sessionId: null,\n103:     completed: false,\n104:     errored: false,\n105:     lastError: null,\n106:     events: [],\n107:   };\n108: \n109:   const lines = rawOutput.split(\"\\n\").filter((l) => l.trim());\n110: \n111:   for (const line of lines) {\n112:     try {\n113:       const event = JSON.parse(line) as OpenCodeEvent;\n114:       result.events.push(event);\n115: \n116:       if (event.sessionID && !result.sessionId) {\n117:         result.sessionId = event.sessionID;\n118:       }\n119: \n120:       if (\n121:         event.type === \"step_finish\" &&\n122:         event.part?.reason === \"stop\"\n123:       ) {\n124:         result.completed = true;\n125:       }\n126: \n127:       if (\n128:         event.type === \"tool_use\" &&\n129:         event.part?.state?.status === \"error\"\n130:       ) {\n131:         result.errored = true;\n132:         result.lastError = event.part.state.error ?? \"unknown tool error\";\n133:       }\n134:     } catch {\n135:       // Not valid JSON — skip\n136:     }\n137:   }\n138: \n139:   return result;\n140: }\n141: \n142: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n143: // Activity Extraction\n144: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n145: \n146: function shortPath(fullPath: string | undefined, maxLen: number = 30): string {\n147:   if (!fullPath) return \"\";\n148:   const parts = fullPath.replace(/^\\/+/, \"\").split(\"/\");\n149:   const short =\n150:     parts.length > 1\n151:       ? parts.slice(-2).join(\"/\")\n152:       : parts[parts.length - 1];\n153:   if (short.length <= maxLen) return short;\n154:   const fname = parts[parts.length - 1];\n155:   return fname.length <= maxLen ? fname : fname.slice(0, maxLen - 1) + \"\\u2026\";\n156: }\n157: \n158: function shortCmd(cmd: string | undefined, maxLen: number = 30): string {\n159:   if (!cmd) return \"\";\n160:   const first = cmd.split(\"\\n\")[0].trim();\n161:   if (first.length <= maxLen) return first;\n162:   return first.slice(0, maxLen - 1) + \"\\u2026\";\n163: }\n164: \n165: /**\n166:  * Map an event to a human-readable activity string.\n167:  */\n168: export function extractActivity(event: OpenCodeEvent): string | null {\n169:   switch (event.type) {\n170:     case \"step_start\":\n171:       return \"thinking\\u2026\";\n172: \n173:     case \"tool_use\": {\n174:       const toolName = (event.part?.tool ?? \"\").toLowerCase();\n175:       const input = event.part?.state?.input ?? {};\n176:       const status = event.part?.state?.status ?? \"\";\n177: \n178:       if (status === \"error\") {\n179:         return `${toolName}: error`;\n180:       }\n181: \n182:       switch (toolName) {\n183:         case \"read\":\n184:           return `reading ${shortPath(input.filePath ?? input.path)}`;\n185:         case \"write\":\n186:           return `writing ${shortPath(input.filePath ?? input.path)}`;\n187:         case \"edit\":\n188:           return `editing ${shortPath(input.filePath ?? input.path)}`;\n189:         case \"bash\":\n190:         case \"command\":\n191:         case \"terminal\": {\n192:           const cmd = input.command ?? input.cmd ?? \"\";\n193:           // Detect HITL ask script invocation\n194:           if (cmd.includes(\"hitl-ask\")) {\n195:             return \"waiting for human…\";\n196:           }\n197:           return `$ ${shortCmd(cmd)}`;\n198:         }\n199:         case \"glob\":\n200:           return `finding: ${shortPath(input.pattern)}`;\n201:         case \"grep\":\n202:         case \"search\":\n203:           return `searching: ${(input.pattern ?? \"\").slice(0, 25)}`;\n204:         case \"task\":\n205:           return \"delegating task\\u2026\";\n206:         case \"webfetch\":\n207:         case \"web_fetch\":\n208:           return \"fetching URL\\u2026\";\n209:         case \"todowrite\":\n210:         case \"todo_write\":\n211:           return \"planning\\u2026\";\n212:         case \"question\":\n213:           return \"asking question\\u2026\";\n214:         case \"jcodemunch_index_folder\":\n215:         case \"jcodemunch_index_repo\":\n216:           return \"indexing code\\u2026\";\n217:         case \"jcodemunch_search_symbols\":\n218:         case \"jcodemunch_search_text\":\n219:           return \"searching symbols\\u2026\";\n220:         case \"jcodemunch_get_file_outline\":\n221:           return `outlining ${shortPath(input.file_path)}`;\n222:         case \"jcodemunch_get_symbol\":\n223:         case \"jcodemunch_get_symbols\":\n224:           return \"reading symbol\\u2026\";\n225:         default:\n226:           return `tool: ${toolName}`;\n227:       }\n228:     }\n229: \n230:     case \"text\":\n231:       return \"responding\\u2026\";\n232: \n233:     case \"step_finish\":\n234:       if (event.part?.reason === \"stop\") return \"done\";\n235:       if (event.part?.reason === \"tool-calls\") return null;\n236:       return null;\n237: \n238:     default:\n239:       return null;\n240:   }\n241: }\n242: \n243: /**\n244:  * Format an event into a human-readable log line for the activity stream.\n245:  */\n246: export function formatEventForLog(event: OpenCodeEvent): string | null {\n247:   switch (event.type) {\n248:     case \"step_start\":\n249:       return \"-- step started\";\n250: \n251:     case \"tool_use\": {\n252:       const toolName = event.part?.tool ?? \"unknown\";\n253:       const input = event.part?.state?.input ?? {};\n254:       const status = event.part?.state?.status ?? \"\";\n255:       const output = event.part?.state?.output ?? \"\";\n256:       const error = event.part?.state?.error ?? \"\";\n257: \n258:       let line = `>> ${toolName}`;\n259:       switch (toolName.toLowerCase()) {\n260:         case \"read\":\n261:           line = `>> read ${shortPath(input.filePath ?? input.path, 50)}`;\n262:           break;\n263:         case \"write\":\n264:           line = `>> write ${shortPath(input.filePath ?? input.path, 50)}`;\n265:           break;\n266:         case \"edit\":\n267:           line = `>> edit ${shortPath(input.filePath ?? input.path, 50)}`;\n268:           break;\n269:         case \"bash\":\n270:         case \"command\":\n271:           line = `>> $ ${shortCmd(input.command ?? input.cmd, 60)}`;\n272:           break;\n273:         case \"glob\":\n274:           line = `>> glob ${input.pattern ?? \"\"}`;\n275:           break;\n276:         case \"grep\":\n277:           line = `>> grep \"${(input.pattern ?? \"\").slice(0, 30)}\"`;\n278:           break;\n279:         case \"task\":\n280:           line = `>> task: ${(input.description ?? input.prompt ?? \"\").slice(0, 50)}`;\n281:           break;\n282:       }\n283: \n284:       if (status === \"completed\" && output) {\n285:         const preview = output.split(\"\\n\")[0].slice(0, 80);\n286:         return `${line}\\n   ${preview}${output.length > 80 ? \"\\u2026\" : \"\"}`;\n287:       }\n288:       if (status === \"error\" && error) {\n289:         return `${line}\\n!! ${error.slice(0, 100)}`;\n290:       }\n291:       return line;\n292:     }\n293: \n294:     case \"text\": {\n295:       const text = event.part?.text ?? \"\";\n296:       if (!text.trim()) return null;\n297:       const firstLine = text.split(\"\\n\").find((l: string) => l.trim())?.trim() ?? \"\";\n298:       if (firstLine.length === 0) return null;\n299:       return `   ${firstLine.slice(0, 120)}${firstLine.length > 120 ? \"\\u2026\" : \"\"}`;\n300:     }\n301: \n302:     case \"step_finish\": {\n303:       const reason = event.part?.reason ?? \"\";\n304:       const tokens = event.part?.tokens;\n305:       if (reason === \"stop\") {\n306:         let tokStr = \"\";\n307:         if (tokens) {\n308:           const parts = [`${tokens.input}in`, `${tokens.output}out`];\n309:           if (tokens.cache?.read) parts.push(`${tokens.cache.read}cache`);\n310:           tokStr = ` (${parts.join(\"/\")})`;\n311:         }\n312:         return `-- done${tokStr}`;\n313:       }\n314:       return null;\n315:     }\n316: \n317:     default:\n318:       return null;\n319:   }\n320: }\n321: \n322: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n323: // Per-agent Activity Log (in-memory ring buffer for TUI)\n324: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n325: \n326: export interface ActivityEntry {\n327:   timestamp: string;\n328:   text: string;\n329: }\n330: \n331: const MAX_ACTIVITY_LINES = 500;\n332: \n333: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n334: // Process Monitor\n335: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n336: \n337: export interface MonitorCallbacks {\n338:   onSessionId?: (featureId: string, sessionId: string) => void;\n339:   onComplete?: (featureId: string) => void;\n340:   onError?: (featureId: string, error: string) => void;\n341:   onOutput?: (featureId: string, data: string) => void;\n342:   onActivity?: (featureId: string, activity: string) => void;\n343:   /** Called when an agent asks a human question via HITL */\n344:   onQuestion?: (featureId: string, questionText: string) => void;\n345:   /** Called when token usage data is parsed from a step_finish event */\n346:   onUsage?: (featureId: string, record: UsageRecord) => void;\n347: }\n348: \n349: interface MonitoredProcess {\n350:   featureId: string;\n351:   process: ChildProcess | null;\n352:   /** Explicit PID — used for reconnected processes where no ChildProcess handle exists */\n353:   pid: number;\n354:   stdout: string;\n355:   stderr: string;\n356:   sessionId: string | null;\n357:   done: boolean;\n358:   lineBuffer: string;\n359:   sawFinalStop: boolean;\n360:   /** True when this entry was created by reconnectProcess() (PID-only, no ChildProcess) */\n361:   reconnected: boolean;\n362: }\n363: \n364: /**\n365:  * Monitor a set of headless agent processes.\n366:  * Collects stdout, parses events, and calls callbacks on state changes.\n367:  */\n368: export class ProcessMonitor {\n369:   private processes: Map<string, MonitoredProcess> = new Map();\n370:   private callbacks: MonitorCallbacks;\n371:   private logDir: string;\n372:   /** Per-agent activity log for TUI preview pane */\n373:   public activityLogs: Map<string, ActivityEntry[]> = new Map();\n374:   /** Token usage collector — parses and accumulates usage from step_finish events */\n375:   public tokenCollector: TokenCollector;\n376:   /** Token usage store — persists records to .wombo-combo/usage.jsonl */\n377:   public usageStore: UsageStore;\n378: \n379:   constructor(projectRoot: string, callbacks: MonitorCallbacks = {}) {\n380:     this.callbacks = callbacks;\n381:     this.logDir = resolve(projectRoot, LOG_DIR_NAME);\n382:     if (!existsSync(this.logDir)) {\n383:       mkdirSync(this.logDir, { recursive: true });\n384:     }\n385:     this.usageStore = new UsageStore(projectRoot);\n386:     this.tokenCollector = new TokenCollector((record) => {\n387:       // Persist to JSONL file for historical tracking\n388:       try {\n389:         this.usageStore.append(record);\n390:       } catch {\n391:         // Non-critical — don't break agent monitoring if write fails\n392:       }\n393:       this.callbacks.onUsage?.(record.task_id, record);\n394:     });\n395:   }\n396: \n397:   private pushActivity(featureId: string, text: string): void {\n398:     if (!this.activityLogs.has(featureId)) {\n399:       this.activityLogs.set(featureId, []);\n400:     }\n401:     const log = this.activityLogs.get(featureId)!;\n402:     for (const line of text.split(\"\\n\")) {\n403:       log.push({ timestamp: new Date().toISOString().slice(11, 19), text: line });\n404:     }\n405:     if (log.length > MAX_ACTIVITY_LINES) {\n406:       log.splice(0, log.length - MAX_ACTIVITY_LINES);\n407:     }\n408:   }\n409: \n410:   private writeLog(featureId: string, data: string): void {\n411:     try {\n412:       const logFile = resolve(this.logDir, `${featureId}.log`);\n413:       appendFileSync(logFile, data);\n414:     } catch {\n415:       // Non-critical\n416:     }\n417:   }\n418: \n419:   getActivityLog(featureId: string): ActivityEntry[] {\n420:     return this.activityLogs.get(featureId) ?? [];\n421:   }\n422: \n423:   addProcess(featureId: string, child: ChildProcess): void {\n424:     const monitored: MonitoredProcess = {\n425:       featureId,\n426:       process: child,\n427:       pid: child.pid!,\n428:       stdout: \"\",\n429:       stderr: \"\",\n430:       sessionId: null,\n431:       done: false,\n432:       lineBuffer: \"\",\n433:       sawFinalStop: false,\n434:       reconnected: false,\n435:     };\n436: \n437:     this.pushActivity(featureId, \"-- agent process started\");\n438:     this.writeLog(featureId, `[wombo] Process started at ${new Date().toISOString()}\\n`);\n439: \n440:     child.stdout?.on(\"data\", (data: Buffer) => {\n441:       const chunk = data.toString();\n442:       monitored.stdout += chunk;\n443:       this.callbacks.onOutput?.(featureId, chunk);\n444:       this.writeLog(featureId, chunk);\n445: \n446:       monitored.lineBuffer += chunk;\n447:       const lines = monitored.lineBuffer.split(\"\\n\");\n448:       monitored.lineBuffer = lines.pop() ?? \"\";\n449: \n450:       for (const line of lines) {\n451:         const trimmed = line.trim();\n452:         if (!trimmed) continue;\n453:         try {\n454:           const event = JSON.parse(trimmed) as OpenCodeEvent;\n455: \n456:           if (!monitored.sessionId && event.sessionID) {\n457:             monitored.sessionId = event.sessionID;\n458:             this.callbacks.onSessionId?.(featureId, event.sessionID);\n459:             this.pushActivity(featureId, `-- session: ${event.sessionID}`);\n460:           }\n461: \n462:           const activity = extractActivity(event);\n463:           if (activity) {\n464:             this.callbacks.onActivity?.(featureId, activity);\n465:           }\n466: \n467:           const logLine = formatEventForLog(event);\n468:           if (logLine) {\n469:             this.pushActivity(featureId, logLine);\n470:           }\n471: \n472:           // Extract token usage from step_finish events\n473:           this.tokenCollector.ingestEvent(featureId, event);\n474: \n475:           if (\n476:             event.type === \"step_finish\" &&\n477:             event.part?.reason === \"stop\"\n478:           ) {\n479:             monitored.sawFinalStop = true;\n480:           }\n481:         } catch {\n482:           if (trimmed.length > 0 && trimmed.length < 500) {\n483:             this.pushActivity(featureId, `[raw] ${trimmed.slice(0, 120)}`);\n484:           }\n485:         }\n486:       }\n487:     });\n488: \n489:     child.stderr?.on(\"data\", (data: Buffer) => {\n490:       const chunk = data.toString();\n491:       monitored.stderr += chunk;\n492:       this.writeLog(featureId, `[stderr] ${chunk}`);\n493:       const lines = chunk.split(\"\\n\").filter((l) => l.trim());\n494:       for (const line of lines) {\n495:         this.pushActivity(featureId, `[stderr] ${line.trim().slice(0, 120)}`);\n496:       }\n497:     });\n498: \n499:     child.on(\"exit\", (code) => {\n500:       monitored.done = true;\n501:       this.pushActivity(featureId, `-- process exited (code ${code})`);\n502:       this.writeLog(featureId, `\\n[wombo] Process exited with code ${code} at ${new Date().toISOString()}\\n`);\n503: \n504:       if (code === 0 || monitored.sawFinalStop) {\n505:         this.callbacks.onComplete?.(featureId);\n506:       } else {\n507:         const error =\n508:           monitored.stderr.slice(-2000) ||\n509:           `Process exited with code ${code}`;\n510:         this.callbacks.onError?.(featureId, error);\n511:       }\n512:     });\n513: \n514:     child.on(\"error\", (err) => {\n515:       monitored.done = true;\n516:       this.pushActivity(featureId, `!! process error: ${err.message}`);\n517:       this.writeLog(featureId, `\\n[wombo] Process error: ${err.message}\\n`);\n518:       this.callbacks.onError?.(featureId, err.message);\n519:     });\n520: \n521:     this.processes.set(featureId, monitored);\n522:   }\n523: \n524:   /**\n525:    * Reconnect to a running agent process by PID.\n526:    *\n527:    * Creates a \"virtual\" MonitoredProcess entry with no ChildProcess handle.\n528:    * This is used when resuming a wave where agents (typically interactive\n529:    * mux-based agents) are still alive but the parent monitor was stopped.\n530:    *\n531:    * Since there are no stdio pipes to read from, this method:\n532:    *   - Loads historical activity from the existing log file (last N lines)\n533:    *   - Starts a PID polling interval to detect process death\n534:    *   - When the PID dies, fires onComplete or onError callbacks based on\n535:    *     whether the agent's worktree has commits (determined by the caller)\n536:    *\n537:    * The polling loop detects PID death and marks the entry as done, which\n538:    * allows the resume.ts polling loop to handle verification/re-launch.\n539:    */\n540:   reconnectProcess(featureId: string, pid: number, sessionId?: string | null): void {\n541:     const monitored: MonitoredProcess = {\n542:       featureId,\n543:       process: null,\n544:       pid,\n545:       stdout: \"\",\n546:       stderr: \"\",\n547:       sessionId: sessionId ?? null,\n548:       done: false,\n549:       lineBuffer: \"\",\n550:       sawFinalStop: false,\n551:       reconnected: true,\n552:     };\n553: \n554:     this.pushActivity(featureId, `-- reconnected to running process (PID ${pid})`);\n555:     this.writeLog(featureId, `\\n[wombo] Reconnected to PID ${pid} at ${new Date().toISOString()}\\n`);\n556: \n557:     // Load historical activity from the log file so the TUI has context\n558:     this._loadHistoricalActivity(featureId);\n559: \n560:     // Start a polling interval to detect PID death.\n561:     // When the PID dies, mark as done and fire the appropriate callback.\n562:     // The resume.ts polling loop will handle verification/re-launch.\n563:     const pollInterval = setInterval(() => {\n564:       if (!isProcessRunning(pid)) {\n565:         clearInterval(pollInterval);\n566:         monitored.done = true;\n567:         this.pushActivity(featureId, `-- reconnected process exited (PID ${pid})`);\n568:         this.writeLog(featureId, `\\n[wombo] Reconnected process PID ${pid} exited at ${new Date().toISOString()}\\n`);\n569:         // Fire onComplete — the resume.ts polling loop checks branchHasChanges\n570:         // and will downgrade to onError/failed if no commits were made.\n571:         this.callbacks.onComplete?.(featureId);\n572:       }\n573:     }, 2000);\n574: \n575:     // Ensure the interval doesn't hold the process alive if everything else is done\n576:     if (pollInterval.unref) {\n577:       pollInterval.unref();\n578:     }\n579: \n580:     this.processes.set(featureId, monitored);\n581:   }\n582: \n583:   /**\n584:    * Load recent lines from the log file into the activity buffer.\n585:    * Gives the TUI context about what the agent was doing before the monitor\n586:    * was stopped.\n587:    */\n588:   private _loadHistoricalActivity(featureId: string): void {\n589:     const logFile = resolve(this.logDir, `${featureId}.log`);\n590:     if (!existsSync(logFile)) return;\n591: \n592:     try {\n593:       const content = readFileSync(logFile, \"utf-8\");\n594:       const lines = content.split(\"\\n\").filter((l) => l.trim());\n595:       // Take last N lines to avoid flooding the activity buffer\n596:       const recentLines = lines.slice(-50);\n597: \n598:       for (const line of recentLines) {\n599:         const trimmed = line.trim();\n600:         if (!trimmed) continue;\n601: \n602:         // Try parsing as JSON event to extract structured activity\n603:         try {\n604:           const event = JSON.parse(trimmed) as OpenCodeEvent;\n605:           const logLine = formatEventForLog(event);\n606:           if (logLine) {\n607:             this.pushActivity(featureId, logLine);\n608:           }\n609:         } catch {\n610:           // Not JSON — add as raw log line (skip [wombo] meta lines)\n611:           if (!trimmed.startsWith(\"[wombo]\")) {\n612:             this.pushActivity(featureId, `[log] ${trimmed.slice(0, 120)}`);\n613:           }\n614:         }\n615:       }\n616:     } catch {\n617:       // Non-critical — log file may be unreadable\n618:     }\n619:   }\n620: \n621:   getSessionId(featureId: string): string | null {\n622:     return this.processes.get(featureId)?.sessionId ?? null;\n623:   }\n624: \n625:   getOutput(featureId: string): string {\n626:     return this.processes.get(featureId)?.stdout ?? \"\";\n627:   }\n628: \n629:   isRunning(featureId: string): boolean {\n630:     const m = this.processes.get(featureId);\n631:     if (!m) return false;\n632:     if (m.done) return false;\n633:     return isProcessRunning(m.pid);\n634:   }\n635: \n636:   allDone(): boolean {\n637:     for (const m of this.processes.values()) {\n638:       if (!m.done) return false;\n639:     }\n640:     return true;\n641:   }\n642: \n643:   activeCount(): number {\n644:     let count = 0;\n645:     for (const m of this.processes.values()) {\n646:       if (!m.done) count++;\n647:     }\n648:     return count;\n649:   }\n650: \n651:   /**\n652:    * Remove a process from monitoring and kill it if still running.\n653:    *\n654:    * Sends SIGTERM (not SIGKILL) to allow the agent to handle shutdown\n655:    * gracefully (e.g., save partial work, close files). The process map\n656:    * entry is deleted immediately — any subsequent events from the dying\n657:    * process are ignored.\n658:    *\n659:    * For reconnected processes (no ChildProcess handle), uses\n660:    * `process.kill(pid, 'SIGTERM')` directly.\n661:    */\n662:   remove(featureId: string): void {\n663:     const m = this.processes.get(featureId);\n664:     if (m && !m.done) {\n665:       try {\n666:         if (m.process) {\n667:           m.process.kill(\"SIGTERM\");\n668:         } else {\n669:           // Reconnected process — no ChildProcess handle, use PID directly\n670:           process.kill(m.pid, \"SIGTERM\");\n671:         }\n672:       } catch {}\n673:     }\n674:     this.processes.delete(featureId);\n675:   }\n676: \n677:   /**\n678:    * Kill all monitored processes. Called during graceful shutdown\n679:    * (SIGINT, TUI quit) to ensure no orphaned agent processes remain.\n680:    *\n681:    * This is the primary teardown path. After killAll(), the parent\n682:    * process saves wave state and exits. Agents can be re-launched\n683:    * later via `woco resume`.\n684:    *\n685:    * Reconnected processes are NOT killed — they are independent agents\n686:    * (typically in mux sessions) that should survive the parent's exit.\n687:    * They are simply removed from the monitor map so polling stops.\n688:    */\n689:   killAll(): void {\n690:     for (const [id, m] of this.processes.entries()) {\n691:       if (m.reconnected) {\n692:         // Don't kill reconnected processes — just stop monitoring\n693:         this.processes.delete(id);\n694:       } else {\n695:         this.remove(id);\n696:       }\n697:     }\n698:   }\n699: \n700:   waitAll(pollIntervalMs: number = 1000): Promise<void> {\n701:     return new Promise((resolve) => {\n702:       const check = () => {\n703:         if (this.allDone()) {\n704:           resolve();\n705:         } else {\n706:           setTimeout(check, pollIntervalMs);\n707:         }\n708:       };\n709:       check();\n710:     });\n711:   }\n712: }\n713: \n714: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n715: // Re-exports from token-collector for convenience\n716: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n717: \n718: export { TokenCollector, type UsageRecord } from \"./token-collector.js\";\n719: export type { UsageSummary, UsageCallback } from \"./token-collector.js\";\n720: \n721: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n722: // Re-exports from token-usage for convenience\n723: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n724: \n725: export { UsageStore, appendUsageRecord, loadUsageRecords, totalUsage, filterByDateRange, groupBy } from \"./token-usage.js\";\n726: export type { UsageTotals, GroupableField } from \"./token-usage.js\";\n\n(End of file - total 726 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/lib/monitor.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * monitor.ts — Parse JSON events from agent and detect completion/failure.\n *\n * Responsibilities:\n *   - Parse newline-delimited JSON events from agent stdout\n *   - Detect session completion (agent finished)\n *   - Detect session ID from events\n *   - Detect errors and failures\n *   - Write per-agent raw log files for diagnostics\n *   - Maintain per-agent parsed activity log for TUI preview\n *\n * ## Process Lifecycle (audit: wave-detach-audit)\n *\n * ProcessMonitor manages the lifecycle of headless agent child processes:\n *\n * **Normal flow**: Agent stdout → JSON event parsing → callbacks → completion\n *   1. `addProcess()` registers a ChildProcess and attaches stdout/stderr listeners\n *   2. Stdout data is parsed line-by-line as JSON events\n *   3. Callbacks fire: `onSessionId`, `onActivity`, `onComplete`, `onError`\n *   4. On process exit (code 0 or sawFinalStop), `onComplete` is called","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773484488747,"end":1773484488750}}}}
