{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773484706045,"sessionID":"ses_31416915cffeaA1eCO5cj4ROyq","part":{"id":"prt_cebed08f7001NBakX4FttcHW4Q","sessionID":"ses_31416915cffeaA1eCO5cj4ROyq","messageID":"msg_cebecfa3f0016wWo74Rz12gUEi","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01TGg5A9BchNW4sJtGTTBdMJ","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/token-tracking/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/token-tracking/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # wombo-combo\n2: \n3: AI agent orchestration for parallel feature development.\n4: \n5: ## Install\n6: \n7: ```sh\n8: # bun\n9: bun a -g wombo-combo\n10: # npm\n11: npm i -g wombo-combo\n12: \n13: # bun (from GitHub)\n14: bun a -g github:fulgidus/wombo-combo\n15: # npm (from GitHub)\n16: npm i -g github:fulgidus/wombo-combo\n17: ```\n18: \n19: ## Quick start\n20: \n21: ```sh\n22: # Initialize project (generates .wombo-combo/config.json and .wombo-combo/tasks.yml)\n23: woco init\n24: \n25: # Edit .wombo-combo/tasks.yml to define your features, then launch the TUI\n26: woco\n27: ```\n28: \n29: Running `woco` with no arguments opens the interactive TUI — a full-screen\n30: task browser where you can evaluate tasks, select them, adjust priorities,\n31: and launch waves of agents. When a wave is running, the TUI switches to a\n32: live monitor showing agent status, activity logs, and build output.\n33: \n34: You can also drive everything from the CLI:\n35: \n36: ```sh\n37: woco launch --all-ready    # launch all tasks with met dependencies\n38: woco status                # show wave status\n39: woco verify                # run build verification\n40: woco merge                 # merge verified branches\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ## Commands\n44: \n45: | Command                               | Description                                       |\n46: | ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |\n47: | `woco`                                | Open interactive TUI (default, no args needed)    |\n48: | `woco init`                           | Generate config in the current project             |\n49: | `woco launch`                         | Launch a wave of agents                            |\n50: | `woco resume`                         | Resume a stopped wave                              |\n51: | `woco status`                         | Show wave status                                   |\n52: | `woco verify`                         | Run build verification                             |\n53: | `woco merge`                          | Merge verified branches                            |\n54: | `woco retry <id>`                     | Retry a failed agent                               |\n55: | `woco abort <id>`                     | Kill a running agent (--requeue to return to queue)|\n56: | `woco logs <id>`                      | View agent logs (--tail N, --follow)               |\n57: | `woco cleanup`                        | Remove worktrees and sessions                      |\n58: | `woco history`                        | List/view past wave results                        |\n59: | `woco tasks list`                     | List tasks                                         |\n60: | `woco tasks add <id> <title>`         | Add a task                                         |\n61: | `woco tasks set-status <id> <status>` | Update task status                                 |\n62: | `woco tasks set-priority <id> <p>`    | Update task priority                               |\n63: | `woco tasks check`                    | Validate tasks file                                |\n64: | `woco tasks show <id>`               | Show task details                                  |\n65: | `woco tasks graph`                    | Visualize dependency graph (--ascii, --mermaid)    |\n66: | `woco upgrade`                        | Check for updates and upgrade                      |\n67: | `woco help`                           | Show full help (also: -h, --help)                  |\n68: \n69: Every command has a short alias (e.g. `woco l` = `woco launch`,\n70: `woco t ls` = `woco tasks list`). Run `woco help` for the full list.\n71: \n72: ## TUI\n73: \n74: The interactive TUI has two views:\n75: \n76: **Task Browser** — browse all tasks organized by dependency streams.\n77: \n78: | Key       | Action                              |\n79: | --------- | ----------------------------------- |\n80: | Space     | Toggle task selection               |\n81: | S         | Toggle entire dependency stream     |\n82: | a         | Select / deselect all               |\n83: | +/-       | Change priority of selected task    |\n84: | d         | Hide / show done tasks              |\n85: | c         | Cycle max concurrency               |\n86: | F5        | Cycle sort field                    |\n87: | L         | Launch selected tasks as a new wave |\n88: | q         | Quit (session is saved)             |\n89: \n90: **Wave Monitor** — shown automatically when a wave is running.\n91: \n92: | Key       | Action                              |\n93: | --------- | ----------------------------------- |\n94: | Up/Down   | Navigate agent list                 |\n95: | Enter     | Attach to agent session / view log  |\n96: | r         | Retry a failed agent                |\n97: | b         | Show build log                      |\n98: | p         | Toggle auto-scroll                  |\n99: | q         | Quit                                |\n100: \n101: Session state (selections, sort, concurrency) is persisted to\n102: `.wombo-combo/tui-session.json` so you can close and reopen without\n103: losing work.\n104: \n105: ## Launch options\n106: \n107: ```sh\n108: woco launch --all-ready              # all features with met dependencies\n109: woco launch --top-priority 3         # top 3 by priority\n110: woco launch --quickest-wins 3        # 3 lowest-effort features\n111: woco launch --tasks \"id1,id2\"        # specific tasks\n112: woco launch --interactive            # tmux TUI mode\n113: woco launch --dry-run                # preview without launching\n114: ```\n115: \n116: ## License\n117: \n118: MIT\n\n(End of file - total 118 lines)\n</content>","title":"README.md","metadata":{"preview":"# wombo-combo\n\nAI agent orchestration for parallel feature development.\n\n## Install\n\n```sh\n# bun\nbun a -g wombo-combo\n# npm\nnpm i -g wombo-combo\n\n# bun (from GitHub)\nbun a -g github:fulgidus/wombo-combo\n# npm (from GitHub)\nnpm i -g github:fulgidus/wombo-combo\n```\n\n## Quick start\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773484706041,"end":1773484706044}}}}
